<br>
A large part of the problem exists due to the relative ease of the quest. Because of this many players are at the final stage in a state of frustration due to their inability to complete the quest quickly, if at all. In hindsight Verant admits that the quest is too easy. However, they refuse to ease the bottleneck so they are content with the status quo. Accept it.<br>
<br>
On to the camp. I've read many threads concerning conflict over the Ragefire camp. While I sympathize with those who feel that their "camp rights" were denied, I also feel that it is time to re-define what it means to camp Ragefire. <br>
<br>
First, let me list a few things that are NOT camping Ragefire:<br>
<br>
<font color=lime><li>Having a Monk or Necro'd feigned in the lair. Also, having any other character sitting around watching for the spawn.<br>
<li>Having a solo Cleric (yourself) sitting in the lair waiting for the spawn.<br>
<li>Keeping the Fire Giants cleared with a small group.<br>
<li>Any amount of players waiting on the spawn that are not sufficient of themselves to kill the spawned Ragefire.</font><br>
<br>
All the above examples are merely an early warning system to allow you to get a head start on gathering the force necessary to kill Ragefire.<br>
<br>
<font color=lime>What is camping Ragefire:<br>
1) A force sufficient to kill Ragefire immediately when he spawns.<br>
2) See 1. above.</font><br>
<br>
When Ragefire spawns, turn in your Shimmering Pearl and kill him. Don't ask for time to buff, for forces to get there, etc. If you can't kill him when he spawns you are not ready. Period. Call in the next group. Ok, I'd probably allow five minutes or so (heck of a time to hit the head), but otherwise you must be ready. If you aren't ready you aren't camping, your scouting.<br>
<br>
Is the above harsh? /em shrugs It's reality. Verant gave us an easy quest. They made the reward for that quest incredibly desirable. That guarantees fierce competition for the reward. With the post from Verant I don't see how one can reasonably treat this camp any other way. The first group at the camp with the force necessary to kill Ragefire gets the spawn (don't dither turning in that pearl). And you know what? It's fair.<br>
<br>
Rayne</i><br>
<br>
<br>
<b>He later clarifies</b><br>
<br>
<br>
<i>Apparently now my May 8 post on Ragefire is now quoted by some as the "guidelines for all Clerics" when it is convenient for some to do so. So if I get to formulate the rules, here they are:<br>
<br>
<li>Ragefire is up and nobody is there. /Cheer yourself. Go for it!<br>
<li>Ragefire is up and one or two people are there. /Cheer yourself, mourn the unlucky, go for it!<br>
<li>Ragefire is up and a questionable group is there. If they aren't planning on spawning quickly (say 15 minutes) tell them sorry, but you aren't ready and we are. Spawn and kill. (Note: if you're the one with the questionable group don't ask for sympathy, etc. They deserve Ragefire too and keeping path clear isn't some huge accomplishment. Sorry, but fact.)<br>
<li>Ragefire is up and a capable group is in the middle of their final preparations for engaging. Congratulate them and come back another time.<br>
<li>If you are already camping Ragefire, um, DO NOT COUNT ON #3 or #4 BEING OBSERVED! Some people just don't care about others. Be strong, be buffed, be ready.<br>
<br>
<br>
<font color=yellow>Because, the only real rule (er, real == Verant) is "mob belongs to Cleric that spawned Ragefire." If you're there first BE the Cleric that spawns Ragefire.</font><br>
<br>
There, my completely "official" Ragefire rules. If you're going to quote me then follow rules 1 - 5. <font color=yellow>If you're going to quote Verant then feel free, but good luck on living with yourself.</font><br>
<br>
And for Xyun who referred to me as "Anon Gimp" I would greatly appreciate it if in the future you would refer to me as "Rayne the Gimp from EQ Cleric." Thanks!<br>
<br>
Oh, and one more thing. Verant, if you go look up "epic" at webster.com nowhere will you see the word "rare" in the definition. Epic means heroic, not rare. Thanks for the situation. <br>
<br>
/rude MyopicPigheadedDevelopers</i><br>
